<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
<bibRefCitation author="Don, G" journalOrPublisher="Nature Methods" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B33" refString="Don, G, 1834. A General History of Dichlamydeous Plants. 3: 725. JG, F Rivington, London." title="A General History of Dichlamydeous Plants. 3: 725. JG, F Rivington, London." year="1834">Don (1834)</bibRefCitation>
recognised the section 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="section" section="Tetrathylax">Tetrathylax</taxonomicName>
(meaning four - pouch) to include 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. quadrilocularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="quadrilocularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">G. quadrilocularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name was formed providing the Greek and Latin translations for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">tetras</emphasis>
(four-fold) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">thylax</emphasis>
(a cell) in recognition of the 4-celled condition of the capsule. de Vriese treated the section at generic rank with the incorrect spelling ' 
<taxonomicName authority="de Vriese" authorityName="de Vriese" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="G.Don" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Goodeniaceae" genus="Tetraphylax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tetraphylax" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Tetraphylax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
', which was followed by subsequent authors until corrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carolin, RC" editor="George, AS" journalOrPublisher="35. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="147 - 281" refId="B21" refString="Carolin, RC, 1992e. Goodenia. In: George, AS, Ed., Flora of Australia vol. 35. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra: 147 - 281" title="Goodenia." volumeTitle="Flora of Australia vol." year="1992 e">Carolin (1992e)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
